<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7613> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7613" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Tr. pl. 100 or 99? In MRR 2.2, note for name and possible background, P. Fourios, dictator tertium at Lanuvium (ILLRP 129a). On the date of his tribunate, see above, on L. Appuleius Saturninus (29). See Wiseman, NM 233, no. 189.\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3674> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3674" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Vetoed, with Marius' support, a bill to recall Metellus Numidicus (App. BC 1.33; Oros. 5.17.11; cf. Dio 28, fr. 95.1-3; Plut. Mar. 31.1). Proposed the confiscation of the properties of Saturninus and his associates (Oros. 5.17.10). See 98, Tribunes of the Plebs, on Decianus." .
